Explore survey data for SEN

author: Mary Fisher

date written: 2025-02-05

Description

Explore the survey data as prep for SEN research questions (analyzing fit - what scale; analyzing homophily, social capital in sn - what attributes). Particularly interested in:

  1. How connected are counties by people who are primarily involved in kelp forest-related issues? <– set scale of SEN

  2. Which organizations have individual responses by people who directly observe kelp, and/or collect and analyze data (info type)? Can I link these organizations to specific restoration sites within counties? <– set scale of SEN

  3. What is the response rate and variation in how respondents are involved in kelp issues (tourism, research, etc)? <– set scale of SEN; is this a useful actor attribute to explore capital

  4. What is the variation in responses on level of involvement in kelp forest issues (primarily, routinely, rarely) <– set scale of SEN

  5. Are there combinations of 1-3 that can help specify who is on the water for scale-setting? (info x involvement type x level involved)

  6. What is the response rate and variation in response for the Question 8 Likert Scale questions on transformation? Variation in response among individuals from the same organization? <– is this a useful actor attribute to explore capital

Notes

Response rates on how / how frequently people engage with kelp related issues are high, and at 100% for those who also provided county info. Same goes for how people get information on kelp related issues.

Most people selected 2+ answers for how they are involved / how they get information. Almost everyone said that they either collect and analyze data OR directly observe change. Individuals who both collect and analyze data and directly observe change represent 33 organizations (out of 54 total)

There is a good range for people who are rarely –> primarily involved in kelp related issues.

Question 8 on goals, riskiness of restoration had 66-69% response rate. Some questions had most respondents agreeing / disagreeing, although there was some variation among individuals belonging to certain organizations. The questions with the most varation… Maybe the organization-level attribute here would be majority disagree / agree / don’t know?

Just for fun…

Whew highly connected network… the only county pairs without the same people / orgs working between them involve Ventura, San Mateo, and San Luis Obispo. the social network density between biologically connected counties will be 1. Will probably want to:

  • be able to look at strength of ties, not just presence / absence (number of orgs collaborating, or something)

  • break down the actor types beyond degree of participation in kelp-related issues

  • build finer-scale ecological network
